Dacryodes edulis

   [5181.jpg]
   Authority (G. Don.) H.J. Lam.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Sapindales:Burseraceae
   Synonyms Canarium edule Hook.f., Canarium saphu Engl., Pachylobus
   edulis G. Don., Pachylobus saphu Engl.
   Common names African plum, bush butter tree, African palm, African
   pear, native pear, bush butter, bafole, bulungu, safoutier, mubafo,
   safu, safu de obo', atangatier
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 5181

   Notes
   Habitat:
   It is a shade-loving species of non-flooded forests in the
   lowland humid tropical zone. Where there is a well-marked
   season, it is found only in gallery forest and on swampy
   ground.
   Environment
   Latitude:
   Altitude: It can be found at elevations up to 1000 m.
   Temperature: It has a wide temperature range.
   Reported temperature range for growth is 14-35°C with the
   optimum between 18-28°C.
   Water: It has a wide rainfall range but is not
   drought resistant. Reported annual rainfall range for
   growth is 1000-5000 mm with the optimum between 1200-3000
   mm.
   Radiation
   Range & intensity: Seedlings thrive in shade, mature
   trees in partly shade to full sunlight.
   Photoperiodism: It adapts well to differences in day
   length.
   Soil:
   Physical: Grows in a wide range of soils and can
   grow on leached, infertile ferrallitic soils.
   Chemical: Estimated soil pH range for growth is 4-8
   with the optimum between 5-6.5.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
